{% set title = "Typography" %}
{% set slug = "typography" %}

{% block content %}
{% include 'reference/_partials/_quick-nav.twig' %}

  <div class="bg-white--tint pad" id="intro">
    <section class="site-container">
      <h2 data-bk-layout class="font-xxl font-thin">{{ title }}</h2>

      <div data-bk-layout="s:9 m:8 l:7" class="rte">
        <p class="font-m">Basekit offers various font classes for very targetted styling.</p>

        <p>Fonts can be fluid or fixes. Fluid fonts will adjust in size between a specified min and max size limits depending on the screen size. Fixed fonts will remain the same size regardless of the screen size. Fluid fonts are ideal for headings short blocks of text while fixed fonts are best suited to long blocks of text.</p>

        <p data-bk-links="primary fade underline-initial down">In addition to the font style classes, a <a href="#rte">rich text content wrapper</a> class is also available that scopes and styles content output from rich text editor fields.</p>
      </div>

      {% include "reference/_partials/_status.twig" with { value : 75 } %}
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-tertiary--lighter pad" id="font-stacks">
    <section class="site-container flex">
      <h3 data-bk-layout class="font-l font-thin">Font Stacks</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="l:4" class="pad-b flex">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-m pad-xs-b flex--start">Default <strong>sans-serif</strong></h4>

          <p>-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 'Helvetica Neue', 'Helvetica', 'Roboto', 'Oxygen', 'Ubuntu', 'Cantarell', 'Fira Sans', 'Droid Sans', 'arial', sans-serif</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="l:4" class="pad-b flex">
        <div class="font-alt">
