  <div class="bg-white--tint pad" id="font-sizes">
    <section class="site-container">
      <h3 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-l">Font Sizes</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="l:7" class="rte">
        <p>In Basekit all headings are set to the same size by default, since it is not necessarily true that you would want a large h1 and a small h4. Sometimes you might want them to be the same size, othertimes it may be have visual weight that does not consist with semantic weight.</p>

        <p>Due to this, Basekit abstracts out font weights and styles to specific utility classes which must be applied to get the desired style. Otherwise all headings and text sizes will, for the most part, remain the same. This also has the added advantage of being able to apply consistent styles to <em>any</em> text elements, regardless of the markup.</p>
      </div>

      <h4 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-m"><b>Fluid</b> Sizes</h4>

      <ol data-bk-layout="pad:0 bottom" class="flex">
        {% for size, val in {'Hero' : 'hero', 'Largest' : 'xxl', 'Larger' : 'xl', 'Large' : 'l'} %}
          <li data-bk-layout="s:6 m:4 l:3" class="flex">
            <dl data-bk-layout="pad:0" class="br-1 ba b-grey shadow bg-white flex flex--content-end">
              <dt data-bk-layout="center" class="font-{{ val }}">Abz</dt>
              <dd data-bk-layout="pad:sm" class="font-s bt b-grey">{{ size }} <code class="float-r">class="<strong>font-{{ val }}</strong>"</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>

      <h4 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-m"><b>Fixed</b> Sizes</h4>

      <ol data-bk-layout="pad:0 bottom" class="flex">
        {% for size, val in {'Medium': 'm', 'Normal': 'n', 'Small': 's', 'Smaller': 'xs'} %}
          <li data-bk-layout="s:6 m:4 l:3" class="flex">
            <dl data-bk-layout="pad:0" class="br-1 ba b-grey shadow bg-white flex flex--content-end">
              <dt data-bk-layout="center" class="font-{{ val }}">Abz</dt>
              <dd data-bk-layout="pad:sm" class="font-s bt b-grey">{{ size }} <code class="float-r">class="<strong>font-{{ val }}</strong>"</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white pad" id="font-weights">
